President Obama announced his intention to nominate three individuals to key administration posts. Elizabeth Littlefield, currently a Director of the World Bank and CEO of the Consultative Group to Assist the Poor (CGAP), is nominated for President of the Overseas Private Investment Corporation. Harry K. Thomas Jr., a career member of the Senior Foreign Service, is nominated for Ambassador to the Republic of the Philippines. David Adelman, a member of the State of Georgia Senate and equity partner at Sutherland Asbill and Brennan LLP, is nominated for Ambassador to the Republic of Singapore. President Obama expressed confidence that these individuals would represent the nation well and strengthen relationships abroad.